    "narrative": "The **Zurich Zebras** enter today\u2019s slate with a high-ceiling core, anchored by **Junior Caminero** (74.54), who presents our most compelling start. Despite a modest park factor, his matchup against Keller benefits significantly from a favorable wind projection, elevating his base expectation into elite territory. We are similarly bullish on our leadoff tandem of **Trea Turner** (70.45) and **Chase Meidroth** (62.45). While **Trea Turner** faces a steady arm in Holmes, his leadoff spot and stolen base utility make him a cornerstone, while **Chase Meidroth** leverages an advantageous platoon edge against Springs to solidify his position as a high-floor producer. In the outfield, **Carson Benge** (67.24) and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (68.47) provide the necessary speed-based upside we prioritize; **Pete Crow-Armstrong** specifically benefits from a strong dynamic platoon advantage, which helps mitigate his poor historical BvP against the opposing starter.\n\nOur roster management remains focused on efficiency, leaving **Josh Smith** (39.29) as the only notable exclusion from the active lineup. While his dynamic platoon profile suggested potential, a combination of an unfavorable matchup against Woo and a dip in his raw projection pushed him just below our 40.0 \"Below Floor\" threshold; we are prioritizing the superior matchup efficiency of **Hyeseong Kim** (62.59) and **Caleb Durbin** (50.64) to maximize our 5x5 categorical output. Meanwhile, we continue to monitor the status of **Christian Yelich**, who remains on the IL, and **Zac Veen**, who is currently logging at-bats with the Albuquerque Isotopes. Owners should be wary of **Gary Sanchez** (46.45); while he is our primary catcher, his production is hampered by a difficult platoon matchup against P\u00e9rez, keeping his score in the marginal range. We will be tracking the lineup closely to ensure no last-minute weather shifts impact the favorable conditions currently projected for **Junior Caminero**.",
